Funktion zur Anzeige von Tweets¶

In [18]:
def show_tweet(link):
    '''Display the contents of a tweet. '''
    url = 'https://publish.twitter.com/oembed?url=%s' % link
    response = requests.get(url)
    html = response.json()["html"]
    display(HTML(html))

Trends bei Hashtag Kookkurrenz¶

In [63]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,5))
hashtags = ['afd', 's21', 'pegida']
colors = ['#17415f', 'red', 'green']
for i, hashtag in enumerate(hashtags):
    var_month = pd.crosstab(index=df.loc[:, 'date'].dt.to_period('M'), 
                            columns=df.loc[:, 'hashtags'].apply(lambda x: x.count(hashtag)))
    var_month[1].plot(ax=ax, color=colors[i])
ax.legend(hashtags)
ax.set_title(label='Trend Hashtag Kookkurrenz', weight='semibold', size=14)
ax.set_xlabel('Monat', size=12)

hashtags = ['corona', 'covid19', 'coronaleugner', 'querdenker']
colors = ['hotpink', 'lavender', 'purple', 'plum']
for i, hashtag in enumerate(hashtags):
    var_month = pd.crosstab(index=df.loc[:, 'date'].dt.to_period('M'), 
                            columns=df.loc[:, 'hashtags'].apply(lambda x: x.count(hashtag)))
    var_month[1].plot(ax=ax, color=colors[i])
ax.legend(hashtags)
ax.set_title(label='Trend Hashtag Kookkurrenz', weight='semibold', size=14)
ax.set_xlabel('Monat', size=12)
ax.set_ylabel('Hufigkeit', size=12)
ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
